## Page Architecture

Every HTML page follows the same structure:

1. `<head>` — charset, viewport, title, meta description, OG tags, canonical URL, inline SVG favicon, Google Fonts preload, `css/styles.css`
2. `<nav>` — fixed top bar, logo `Noein.`, links, hamburger toggle, `.nav-cta`
3. Page-specific content sections
4. `<footer>` — brand, page links, contact info
5. `<script src="js/main.js">`

Nav and footer are **duplicated** across all 6 pages — edits must be mirrored manually.

## JavaScript Modules (within single IIFE)

| Feature | Selector / Trigger | Behavior |
|---------|-------------------|----------|
| Fade-in | `.fade-in` | IntersectionObserver adds `.visible` |
| Stat counters | `.stat-number[data-count]` | Animated count-up on `.stats` section entering viewport |
| Nav scroll | `nav` | Adds `.nav-scrolled` after 50px scroll |
| Active link | `.nav-links a` | Matches pathname to set `.nav-active` |
| Hamburger | `.nav-toggle` | Toggles `.open` / `.active` on menu |
| Smooth scroll | `a[href^="#"]` | `scrollIntoView` for same-page anchors |
| Accordion | `.case-card-header` | Toggles `.open` (one open at a time) |
| Form validation | `.contact-form form` | Client-side required + email regex check |
| Tab switching | `[data-tab]` | Switches `.contact-tab--active`, reads hash on load |

## CSS Organization (comment banner sections in styles.css)

Global reset & tokens → Navigation → Buttons → Hero → Stats → Logo bar → Sections → Value props → Services grid → Capsar (pain grid, steps, comparison) → Case studies → Contact (layout, form, tabs) → Footer → Responsive breakpoints → Print & accessibility

